race.description: Fulmen Park I Wish I Win Handicap (Bm84)
race.comment: BIG SWINGER (1) looks to have found his right race third up. He was heavily supported first up in Listed company at Flemington with improvement to come, running a solid third on tough ground. He was no match for the first couple (Here To Shock & Persian Spirit) at Caulfield but ran well for third and we should see that form hold up earlier. This is far easier and he rates highly even with the big weight. DIRTY GRIN (9) was a sharp winner first up with 61kg at Geelong. He's always promised a bit and is up to this. RECON (17) is flying having won two in a row and will take holding out. HEART OF GLASS (16) resumes with a good overall strike rate and the ability to reel off some big late splits.
